          </div>
        </div>
      ))}

      <h2>Where to Buy Harmonium in India</h2>
      <p><strong>Music Stores:</strong> The best option — you can test the instrument, check tuning, and return if defective. Look for established music stores in your city, especially in music hubs like Delhi's Darya Ganj, Mumbai's Falkland Road, or Chennai's Subramanian Street.</p>
      <p><strong>Online:</strong> Amazon.in and Flipkart carry major brands. Buy only from verified sellers with return policies. Read reviews carefully — look specifically for comments about tuning quality.</p>
      <p><strong>Direct from manufacturer:</strong> Bina Harmonium in Delhi and some Kolkata-based manufacturers sell directly at factory prices.</p>

      <h2>Final Recommendation</h2>
      <p>For most beginners, we recommend the <strong>Paloma BH-39</strong> (₹6,000–₹8,000) for best value, or the <strong>Bina No. 17 Deluxe</strong> (₹8,500–₹11,000) if you can stretch the budget. Both will serve you well through beginner and intermediate stages without needing replacement.</p>

